cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.AI, cs.IR. 

The paper deals with computer vision tasks such as human segmentation and video segmentation, which are typically categorized under cs.CV. The paper also proposes a weakly supervised learning framework using deep convolutional neural networks, which falls under cs.LG. The use of unsupervised video segmentation and graph optimization techniques also suggests the possibility of cs.MM and cs.AI. Finally, the paper mentions the use of PASCAL VOC 2012 dataset, which is commonly used in information retrieval tasks, indicating a possible connection to cs.IR.
